WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:12.656
Welcome to the Findings tutorial. A finding is one deterministic rule match. Review it independently before accepting the incident that contains it.

2
00:00:14.056 --> 00:00:20.272
We load the fixed SSH sample so every learner sees the same evidence and the same four findings.

3
00:00:21.672 --> 00:00:31.656
The list shows title, severity, confidence, event count, and MITRE technique. Clicking a finding card changes the evidence preview beside it.

4
00:00:33.056 --> 00:00:43.592
We select a finding and compare its reason with the numbered raw lines. Confidence describes the rule match; it does not remove the possibility of a false positive.

5
00:00:44.992 --> 00:00:56.824
We click Rule to open the exact versioned detection definition. The Library explains matching logic, correlation behavior, false positives, and recommended analyst steps.

6
00:00:58.224 --> 00:01:08.232
Returning to Findings preserves the selected detection. The workflow is deliberate: signal, evidence, rule logic, and only then a conclusion.
